solutionCode.javascript:
    ```javascript
function canDestroyAll(mass, asteroids) {
    asteroids.sort((a, b) => a - b);
    for (const asteroid of asteroids) {
        if (mass >= asteroid) {
            mass += asteroid;
        } else {
            return false;
        }
    }
    return true;
}
```

    - Sort the asteroids array in ascending order.
- Iterate through the sorted asteroids array.
- At each iteration, check if the planet's mass is greater than or equal to the asteroid's mass.
  - If it is, add the asteroid's mass to the planet's mass.
  - If it isn't, return `false` because the planet cannot destroy all asteroids.
- If the iteration completes successfully, return `true` as the planet can destroy all asteroids.

